value.value: The number of times to multiply by a number.
The highest power of any term in a polynomial.
A name/value parameter passed into an analytical routine.
A mixing parameter typically giving a degree of smoothing used, or a relaxation parameter defining a rate of convergence.
Not far distant in time or space or degree or circumstances.
Used to indicate that either or both of two items or options may be valid.
A smoothing parameter.

A neoplasm that arises from the organs that comprise the urinary system and is characterized by the absence of atypical or malignant cytological and architectural features, and absence of invasive features or metastatic potential.
Leave undone or leave out; get rid of.
A unit used by the Food and Drug Administration (FDA).
Not controlled, regulated, or constrained.
A term that expresses the function of a gene product.

A scoring system used to determine the grade of invasive breast carcinoma.  The total score is determined by the summation of three values (scores), each numbered 1-3.  The three values correspond to the degree of tubular formation, the degree of nuclear pleomorphism, and the mitotic counts per 10 high power fields, respectively.  The sum of the three values produces a total score of 3-9.  Lesions with total score 3-5, are grade I; lesions with total score 6-7, are grade 2.  Lesions with total score 8-9, are grade 3.
Surgical removal of the lymph nodes located in a particular anatomic region.  This procedure is commonly performed as a component of cancer staging.
The surgical removal of all or part of the lymph nodes that drain lymph from the area around a tumor.
The act of measuring or estimating a quantity.
A procedure to determine the number of cells in a sample.
The portion of the bladder that is formed by the posterior wall and is located opposite to the bladder opening.
A neoplastic endometrial proliferation that is confined to the endometrium and does not have metastatic potential.
The tissue layers that form the urinary bladder. They include the mucosa, submucosa, smooth muscle, and serosa.
The epithelium of the bronchioles of the lung, which consists of cuboidal cells.
One of the three lobes that comprise the right lung.
Either of the two (upper or lower) lobes that comprise the left lung.
A vein that returns oxygenated blood from the left lung to the left atrium of the heart.
A vein that returns oxygenated blood from the right lung to the left atrium of the heart.

A self-administered instrument designed to measure energy expenditure or physical fitness. It was originally developed to measure quality of life achieved by patients in rehabilitation programs for chronic obstructive pulmonary disease, but has also been used as a measure of physical activity in both healthy and impaired populations. The profile consists of 94 common daily activities listed in ascending order according to the energy required to perform them. Activities including self-care tasks, personal/household work, entertainment/social activities, and independent exercise pursuits and respondents are requested to indicate if they are currently able to perform the activity (unassisted), they have stopped performing the activity, or they have never performed the activity.
A rectangular area in a city surrounded by streets and usually containing several buildings.

A neoplasm that arises from the adrenal medulla and is characterized by the absence of atypical or malignant cytological and architectural features, and absence of invasive features or metastatic potential.
The entrance through which you enter or leave a room or building used as an element of an address.
A locality or minor thoroughfare the address for which must be specified in relationship to a more major one.
A land mass smaller than a continent that is surrounded by water.
A tract of land cultivated for the purpose of agricultural production or devoted to the raising and breeding of domestic animals.
A district administered by a prefect (as in France or Japan).
An area of land or sea that has been divided from other areas and is controlled by a particular country. (from Cambridge Dictionaries Online)
A distinct region or subdivision of a territorial or political area or community.
A structure taller than its diameter; can stand alone or be attached to a larger building.
A community of people smaller than a town.
A small administrative division of a country.
A finding of leukemia that is not growing and responds to treatment
A way of access consisting of a set of steps used as an element of an address.

A self-limiting, rapidly growing, non-encapsulated benign neoplasm arising from the subcutaneous tissues. It is characterized by the growth of plump spindle-shaped fibroblasts in a storiform pattern, multinucleated osteoclast-like giant cells, red blood cell extravasation, chronic inflammatory cells, and high mitotic activity.
Cytidine deaminase (146 aa, ~16 kDa) is encoded by the human CDA gene. This protein is involved in the deamination of cytidine and deoxycytidine to uridine and deoxyuridine, respectively.
This gene plays a role in signal transduction and is putatively involved in cytoskeletal remodeling.

Signal-induced proliferation-associated protein 1 (1042 aa, ~112 kD) is encoded by the human SIPA1 gene. This protein is localized to the nucleus and functions as a GTPase activator for the nuclear Ras-related regulatory proteins.
An antibody acting against tissues of the organism that produces it.

label.value: Breast Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v6

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of breast cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system. TNM clinical findings are based on information obtained prior to the first definitive treatment through physical examination, diagnostic imaging, endoscopy, biopsy or laboratory testing.

label.value: Breast Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of breast cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system. TNM pathologic findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

label.value: Breast Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of breast cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor. TNM pathologic primary tumor findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.
